From: PS4 Linux Baikal Port <noreply@ps4-linux>
Subject: [PATCH] amdgpu: v25 - remove 1080p120 mode, mark 1080p60 preferred

Per the PS4-on-Linux community guide:

  "If you lose signal or get an 'unsupported resolution' error from
   your TV/monitor right after booting or BEFORE seeing the login
   screen, then you must change to a different kernel, as some kernels
   try to run the PS4 in 120hz mode (no, it doesn't show anything on
   a high refresh-rate capable display)"

ps4_bridge_get_modes was adding both mode_1080p (VIC 16, 60Hz) AND
mode_1080p120 (VIC 63, 120Hz). Some logic path may pick 120Hz which
the bridge can't actually output cleanly to most displays -> blank.

Remove mode_1080p120 from get_modes, mark 1080p60 as PREFERRED, and
return count=1 so DRM probe knows we have exactly one mode.

Combined with v24's mode_fixup (forces adjusted_mode to 1080p), DRM
should now ALWAYS run the GPU at 1080p60.

Also bumps return value from 0 to 1 — drm_helper_probe_single_connector_modes
treats 0 as "no modes found" and might not use our probed mode.

---
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/ps4_bridge.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/ps4_bridge.c
@@ -703,20 +703,23 @@
 	struct drm_display_mode *newmode;
 	pr_info("ps4_bridge_get_modes\n");
 
+	/* v25: ONLY expose 1080p60 and mark it preferred. The PS4-on-Linux
+	 * community guide specifically calls out that 120Hz mode causes
+	 * "unsupported resolution" and no signal on real displays:
+	 *
+	 *   "Some kernels try to run the PS4 in 120hz mode (no, it doesn't
+	 *    show anything on a high refresh-rate capable display)"
+	 *
+	 * Removing mode_1080p120 forces DRM to pick 1080p60 as the only
+	 * available CEA mode. Marking PREFERRED so DRM's mode-pick logic
+	 * favors it over any user-mode alternatives. */
 	newmode = drm_mode_duplicate(dev, &mode_1080p);
+	newmode->type |= DRM_MODE_TYPE_PREFERRED;
 	drm_mode_probed_add(connector, newmode);
 
-	newmode = drm_mode_duplicate(dev, &mode_1080p120);
-	drm_mode_probed_add(connector, newmode);
-
-	//newmode = drm_mode_duplicate(dev, &mode_720p);
-	//drm_mode_probed_add(connector, newmode);
-	//newmode = drm_mode_duplicate(dev, &mode_480p);
-	//drm_mode_probed_add(connector, newmode);
-
 	drm_connector_update_edid_property(connector, NULL);
 
-	return 0;
+	return 1;
 }
 
 enum drm_connector_status ps4_bridge_detect(struct drm_connector *connector,
